# Arabic & RTL Conventions

This app's primary locale is `ar_SA`. All user-facing strings must be in Arabic, and all layouts must work correctly under RTL (right-to-left) directionality.

## User-Facing Strings

- Write every user-visible string in Arabic. No English UI text.
- Keep debug/log messages and code identifiers (class, method, variable names) in English.

```dart
// BAD
Text('Save')
Text('Customer Name')

// GOOD
Text('حفظ')
Text('اسم العميل')
```

## RTL-Safe Layout

- Use logical directional properties instead of left/right.
  - `EdgeInsetsDirectional` instead of `EdgeInsets.only(left/right: ...)`
  - `AlignmentDirectional.centerStart/centerEnd` instead of `Alignment.centerLeft/centerRight`
  - `PositionedDirectional` instead of `Positioned` when using `left`/`right`.
  - `BorderRadiusDirectional` when the radius is side-specific.
- Prefer `start`/`end` params in widgets (e.g., `Padding(padding: EdgeInsetsDirectional.only(start: 8))`).
- Use `TextAlign.start` / `TextAlign.end` instead of `left` / `right`.
- Do NOT wrap widgets in `Directionality(textDirection: TextDirection.ltr)` unless the content is inherently LTR (e.g., rendering a raw phone number, IBAN, barcode, or code snippet).

```dart
// BAD
Padding(padding: EdgeInsets.only(left: 16), child: ...)
Align(alignment: Alignment.centerLeft, child: ...)

// GOOD
Padding(padding: EdgeInsetsDirectional.only(start: 16), child: ...)
Align(alignment: AlignmentDirectional.centerStart, child: ...)
```

## Icons

- Use directional icon variants (`Icons.arrow_back_ios` → prefer `Icons.arrow_back_ios_new` only when non-directional; otherwise use `Icons.arrow_forward` so Flutter mirrors it under RTL automatically when the icon supports it).
- For chevrons/arrows that must follow reading direction, rely on Flutter's auto-mirroring rather than hardcoding left/right.

## Numbers, Dates, Currency

- Display numbers using Western digits (0-9) unless the user explicitly requests Arabic-Indic digits.
- Format currency and dates via `intl` with locale `ar_SA` when formatting is needed; never concatenate strings manually.

## Do Not

- Do NOT add new `supportedLocales` or change the app `locale` away from `ar_SA` without an explicit request.
- Do NOT introduce hardcoded `TextDirection.ltr` at the screen or app level.
